# TZ-104 — Pi-* UI-kit adoption audit + targeted migration

| | |
|---|---|
| **Status** | ⏳ READY (audit complete, plan adopted) |
| **Scope** | Frontend Angular 20 Pi-* adoption across 30+ pages + 1 pi-table expansion |
| **Target TZ** | TZ-104 (independent sub-tasks; depends on TZ-103 dialog infra being stable) |
| **Depends on** | TZ-103 (PiDialogService — must land FIRST so consumer migration doesn't typecheck-fail mid-stream); TZ-95 (Pi-* utilities convention); TZ-90B (modal=true default — applies only to dialog route, not forms) |
| **Typecheck gate** | `cd frontend && pnpm exec tsc -p tsconfig.app.json --noEmit` → exit 0 |
| **Adoption gate** | `ripgrep '<table', '<button role="switch"', '<input type="checkbox">', native '<select>' in pages/*.page.ts shows ZERO unapproved matches |
| **Browser gate** | All 30+ list-page / form-dialog pages render identical to pre-TZ-104 baseline; no visual regression |

---

## 1. Цель / Problem statement (2026-07-12 audit)

User request:

> "провести проверку на пирей использования компонентов" — check Pi-* UI-kit adoption
> "если мы поменяем там то везде тоже должно поменяться поведение" — changes in UI-kit must propagate everywhere
> "все ли происходит именно через пили использованы компоненты" — every component uses Pi-*

**Audit findings** (via ripgrep on `<app-pi-X` in `frontend/src/app/`):

- **CRITICAL off-path primitives** (Pi-* exists, pages bypass it):
  1. `<app-pi-table>` (in `shared/ui/pi-table.component.ts`) — used only in 1 file (its own spec). 27 list-pages hand-roll native `<table>`.
  2. `<app-pi-input>` — 0 files. Pages use native `<input>`.
  3. `<app-pi-textarea>` — 0 files. Pages use native `<textarea>`.
  4. `<app-pi-popover>` — 0 files. (May be acceptable if PiSheet / PiDrawer used instead.)
  5. `<app-pi-menu>` — 0 page files (only inside shared/ui menu component).
- **MEDIUM off-path primitives** (under-adopted):
  6. `<app-pi-checkbox>` — 1 file (forms.page.ts kit showcase only).
  7. `<app-pi-switch>` — 1 file (builder-inspector.component.ts only).
  8. `<app-pi-radio>` — only inside shared/ui/radio; pages use raw list with `class="peer"` styling.
  9. `<app-pi-select>` — 2-3 files (forms, builder, builder-inspector); NOT in form-dialogs.
  10. `<app-pi-tabs>` — 1 file (navigation.page.ts kit showcase only).
  11. `<app-pi-card>` — 3 files (foundations, basics, theme-editor only).
- **HIGH adoption** (good):
  12. `<app-pi-form-field>` — 61 sites / 12 files.
  13. `<app-pi-section>` — 63 sites / 18 files.
  14. `<app-pi-button>` — 92 sites / 30+ files.
  15. `<app-pi-empty-state>` — 27 sites / 14 files.
  16. `<app-pi-page-header>` — 24 sites / 24 files.
  17. `<app-pi-toolbar>` — 12 sites / 12 files.
  18. `<app-pi-row-actions>` — 10 sites / 10 files.
  19. `<app-pi-dialog>` — 7 form-dialogs + 1 spec.

**Net assessment:** the UI-kit exists for ~46 primitives but ~7 critical primitives have zero or near-zero page-level adoption. This actively prevents the user's "change in UI-kit → propagate everywhere" expectation.

