## 2. Audit details — per offender

### 2.1 Native `<table>` in 27 list-pages (CRITICAL)

| File | Lines / pattern |
|---|---|
| `texts.page.ts` (TZ-86) | `<table class="w-full text-sm">` + manual `<thead class="hairline-b">` + `<th class="pi-cell eyebrow">` + inline `<tbody>` row templates |
| `tables.page.ts` (TZ-86) | same pattern, sortable headers |
| `products.page.ts` (TZ-83) | same pattern |
| `work-types.page.ts` (TZ-83B) | same pattern, sortable |
| `orders.page.ts` (TZ-83C) | same pattern |
| `organizations.page.ts` (TZ-83) | same pattern |
| `dictionaries.page.ts` (TZ-NEW) | same pattern |
| `materials.page.ts` (TZ-19) | same pattern |
| `contracts.page.ts` (TZ-NEW) | same pattern |
| `modules.page.ts` + `module-detail.page.ts` (TZ-83) | similar |
| `doc-constructor/{builder,texts,tables}.page.ts` (TZ-86) | builder has its own canvas component |
| `inventory/{storage-items,stock-movements,inventory-dashboard}.page.ts` (TZ-100/101) | similar |

**pi-table component exists** at `shared/ui/pi-table.component.ts` (and `.spec.ts`). It is referenced ONLY by its own spec file. Pages don't use it because:
- **Feature gap (likely):** it doesn't support sortable headers, sticky cells, expansion rows, action columns, paginated server-side data, or row-level click handlers to the extent each list-page needs.
- **No migration call to action**: no TZ has previously directed pages to migrate.

### 2.2 Native `<button role="switch">` in 8+ list-pages (MEDIUM)

Hand-rolled isActive toggle pattern (texts.page.ts line ~89, products.page.ts line ~93, orders.page.ts line ~115, etc.). All look ~identical:

```html
<button
  type="button" role="switch" [attr.aria-checked]="row.isActive"
  (click)="onToggleActive(row)"
  class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-9 h-5 rounded-full transition-colors"
  [class.bg-sunrise-warm]="row.isActive"
  [class.bg-rule]="!row.isActive"
  ...
>
  <span class="block w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-paper transition-transform" ...></span>
</button>
```

`<app-pi-switch>` exists in `shared/ui/switch/` and is correctly used in `builder-inspector.component.ts` (lines 82, 88). Adoption blocker: zero enforcement + extra hand-rolled widget in pages took root first.

### 2.3 Native `<input type="checkbox">` in 3 form-dialogs (MEDIUM)

`product-form-dialog.component.ts` (~line 190), `material-form-dialog.component.ts`, `order-form-dialog.component.ts` all use raw `<input type="checkbox">` for isActive toggle. Pi-checkbox exists in shared/ui/checkbox (`forms.page.ts` uses it). Straightforward wrap replacement.

### 2.4 Native `<textarea>` in form-dialogs (MEDIUM)

`text-block-dialog.component.ts` line ~120 (markdown editor), `builder-inspector.component.ts` content editor use raw `<textarea>` with `class="pi-input font-mono"`. Pi-textarea exists but has 0 usage.

### 2.5 Native `<select>` in form-dialogs (LOW)

`product-form-dialog.component.ts` line ~249 (`dimUnit` select), `material-form-dialog.component.ts` similar. Pi-select exists + works (forms.page.ts uses it). Replaceable but requires option-array API understanding.

### 2.6 Pi-card / Pi-tabs / Pi-popover / Pi-menu — underused

These may be acceptable (kit-only showcase) or require separate decisions:
- **Pi-tabs:** outside-kit nav uses `PiNavDropdown` family instead. Intentional? Worth confirming.
- **Pi-card:** only kit showcase uses. Pages don't need cards (lists + dialogs suffice for now).
- **Pi-popover:** may be intentionally absent (PiTooltip + PiSheet + PiDrawer cover the use cases).
- **Pi-menu:** used internally by PiDropdownMenu; pages don't need direct menu usage.

