## 3. Архитектурные решения

### 3.1 Selected option: **Option H — Targeted sub-tasks**

Sweep (Option G) is too destructive. Adoption tool (Option J) is awareness-only. Source-of-truth enforcement (Option I) doesn't fix existing gaps. Option H isolates risk per primitive.

### 3.2 Why Option H

- **TZ-103 dependency** must land BEFORE TZ-104.1 + 104.2 (consumers modify dialog body code). Targeted sub-tasks respect this.
- **Reviewability.** Smaller PRs (~150-1500 LOC scoped to a primitive) are merged faster + clearer rollback semantics.
- **Pi-table expansion is its own concern.** §4.3 covers it separately — feature parity BEFORE adoption is the only sane migration path; otherwise pages regress.

### 3.3 What is NOT in scope

- Pi-card / Pi-tabs / Pi-popover / Pi-menu — see §2.6; deferred until a real consumer use-case arises.
- TZ-103 retry — already shipped (TZ-103 covered dialog bugs from prior turn).
- Style audit (OKLCH hex codes vs. var(--pi-*) tokens) — addressed in §7.6 below.
- Documentation rewrite of `docs/paper-and-ink.md` — modified in lockstep with TZ-104.3 only; TZ-104.1 + 104.2 are code-only.

---

## 4. Sub-task breakdown (TZ-104.1 / 104.2 / 104.3)

**Execution ordering (explicit):**

```
TZ-103 (PiDialogService refactor)  ← must MERGE first
      ↓
TZ-104.1 (form primitives)       ← 5 form-dialogs; ~150 LOC
      ↓
TZ-104.2 (switches)              ← 8+ list-pages; ~100 LOC; can run IN PARALLEL with 104.1
      ↓
TZ-104.3 (pi-table expansion)    ← shared/ui/pi-table.component.ts; ~300 LOC
      ↓
TZ-104.3 (table adoption)        ← 27 list-pages; ~1500 LOC; must run AFTER expansion ships
```

Note: TZ-104.1 MUST be after TZ-103 merge. **TZ-104.2 vs TZ-104.1 parallel strategy (Nit #1 resolved):** Two-branch parallel model. `branch-a` carries TZ-104.1 + 104.2 serial (104.2 reuses 104.1's `inject(DestroyRef)` infrastructure pattern for consistency); `branch-b` carries TZ-104.3 (independent file surface). Merge `branch-a` after each sub-task validation, then start `branch-b`. Visual A/B compare on pi-switch is therefore performed post-merge, not in parallel branches. TZ-104.3 has TWO phases (expansion then adoption) — neither can run before TZ-103.

### 4.1 TZ-104.1 — Form primitive swap (closes native `<input type="checkbox">`, `<textarea>`, `<select>`)

**Files (5):**
- `frontend/src/app/pages/products/product-form-dialog.component.ts`
- `frontend/src/app/pages/materials/material-form-dialog.component.ts`
- `frontend/src/app/pages/orders/order-form-dialog.component.ts`
- `frontend/src/app/pages/doc-constructor/texts/text-block-dialog.component.ts` (textarea)
- `frontend/src/app/pages/doc-constructor/builder/builder-inspector.component.ts` (textarea)

**Migrations:**

```ts
// BEFORE (product-form-dialog.component.ts line ~190):
<input type="checkbox" formControlName="isActive" name="isActive" />

// AFTER:
<app-pi-checkbox formControlName="isActive" name="isActive" />

// BEFORE (text-block-dialog.component.ts line ~120):
<textarea
  class="pi-input w-full font-mono text-xs"
  rows="14"
  formControlName="content" name="content"
  placeholder="..."
/>

// AFTER:
<app-pi-textarea
  rows="14" mono
  formControlName="content" name="content"
  placeholder="..."
/>

// BEFORE (product-form-dialog.component.ts line ~249):
<select id="prod-dimUnit" formControlName="dimUnit" class="pi-input w-full">
  <option value="m">м</option>
  <option value="cm">см</option>
  ...
</select>

// AFTER: convert to pi-selectOption pattern (matches forms.page.ts):
<app-pi-select formControlName="dimUnit" ariaLabel="Единица">
  <app-pi-select-option value="m">м</app-pi-select-option>
  <app-pi-select-option value="cm">см</app-pi-select-option>
  ...
</app-pi-select>
```

**Acceptance criteria:**
- `grep -rn '<input type="checkbox"' frontend/src/app/pages/{products,materials,orders}/form-dialog --include='*.ts'` returns 0
- `grep -rn '<textarea' frontend/src/app/pages/{doc-constructor/{texts,builder},products,materials,orders} --include='*.ts'` returns 0 (acceptable: exclude textarea inside pi-textarea component itself)
- `grep -rn '<select ' frontend/src/app/pages/{products,materials,orders}/form-dialog --include='*.ts'` returns 0

**Scope:** ~150 LOC across 5 files. **Test impact:** LOW (reactive form bindings largely unaffected).

