## 6. Migration steps (in order)

1. **Verify TZ-103 is merged.** `git log origin/main --oneline | grep TZ-103`. If not, halt TZ-104 until TZ-103 ships.
2. **Inventory grep runs:**
   - `grep -rn '<button[^>]*role="switch"' frontend/src/app/pages --include='*.ts' | wc -l` → expect N1 sites
   - `grep -rn '<input type="checkbox"' frontend/src/app/pages/{products,materials,orders} --include='*.ts' | wc -l` → expect N2 sites
   - `grep -rn '<select ' frontend/src/app/pages/{products,materials,orders} --include='*.ts' | wc -l` → expect N3 sites
   - `grep -rln '<table.*pi-cell eyebrow' frontend/src/app/pages --include='*.ts' | wc -l` → expect ~27 files
3. **TZ-104.1 implementation:**
   - Replace `<input type="checkbox">` → `<app-pi-checkbox>` (3 files)
   - Replace `<textarea>` → `<app-pi-textarea>` (2 files)
   - Replace `<select>` → `<app-pi-select>` (3 files, with option-list conversion)
   - Typecheck, atomic commit.
4. **TZ-104.2 implementation:**
   - Replace `<button role="switch">` → `<app-pi-switch>` (8-10 files)
   - Verify visual diff via browser-use ±10%
   - Typecheck, atomic commit (per page or batched 4 pages).
5. **TZ-104.3 Phase A:** expand `pi-table.component.ts` API (sortable, sticky, action, pagination, empty). Atomic commit.
6. **TZ-104.3 Phase B:** batch-migrate 27 pages (5-8 per atomic commit, with browser smoke after each batch).
7. **Docs sync:** `docs/paper-and-ink.md` updated to reflect new Pi-* coverage.
8. **Code-reviewer on each commit.**
9. **`git push origin main`** after each batch.

---

## 7. Cross-cutting concerns

### 7.1 Pi-table feature parity FIRST

TZ-104.3 Phase A (shared/ui expansion) MUST come before Phase B (page adoption). Otherwise pages regress. Expansion is the higher-risk phase; budget 60% of TZ-104.3 time for Phase A.

### 7.2 OKLCH token consistency

Pages have CSS like `[class.bg-sunrise-warm]` on raw buttons. After migration to pi-switch, this should be pi-switch default (yellow). Verify visually no regression.

Similarly, `[class.text-destructive]`, `[class.bg-rule]`, `[class.text-muted]` are OKLCH tokens already — pi-* primitives should use the same token names to ensure palette changes in theme-editor propagate correctly.

### 7.3 `data-test` propagation

`<app-pi-checkbox>`, `<app-pi-switch>`, `<app-pi-textarea>`, `<app-pi-select>` MUST forward `data-test` attributes to the underlying native element so E2E selectors don't break after migration.

### 7.4 TZ-103 prereq dependence

Migration of form-dialogs touches the same code TZ-103 modifies. **TZ-103 must be merged first.** A pending TZ-103 is a hard blocker for TZ-104.1.

### 7.5 Test impact estimates

- TZ-104.1: <10% of affected pages have spec files; low impact.
- TZ-104.2: ~50% of affected pages have spec files; medium impact. Spec assertions `hostEl.querySelector('button[role=switch]')` will need updating to `hostEl.querySelector('[role=switch]')` (pi-switch's host role = switch).
- TZ-104.3: 80% of affected pages have spec files; HIGH. Spec assertions like `fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('table tbody tr')` need replacing with `app-pi-table` content. **Plan for substantial spec rewrite cost.**

### 7.6 Style consistency / docs

`docs/paper-and-ink.md` should be updated in tandem with TZ-104.3 to list the expanded `pi-table` API. Otherwise kit discoverability stays inconsistent.

