## 9. Out of scope (explicit)

- ❌ Pi-card / Pi-tabs / Pi-popover / Pi-menu full adoption — currently kit-only. Defer until a consumer need arises.
- ❌ Style migration from Tailwind hex/OKLCH class strings to design-token CSS vars (can span TZ-95-extend).
- ❌ A11y pass beyond aria-label forwarding (defer to TZ-95 / TZ-90 accessibility).
- ❌ Refactoring of page-level state management (signals vs. RxJS consistency) — separate concern.
- ❌ Pi-table inline-edit cells (TZ-CRM, eventual).
- ❌ Pi-table reordering rows via drag-drop (separate spec if needed).

---

## 10. Risk callouts

| # | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| R-1 | **TZ-103 prereq** — consumer migration mid-stream risk | HIGH | Hard-block TZ-104 until TZ-103 ships (verify via `git log origin/main`) |
| R-2 | pi-table feature parity gap — pages lose sortable/sticky/action features if expansion incomplete | HIGH | Phase A MUST finish + pass kit spec before Phase B starts |
| R-3 | Spec files break post-migration (TABLE / button[role=switch] / input[checkbox] no longer in DOM) | MEDIUM | Per-page spec rewrite cost budgeted; re-author affected specs as part of migration batch |
| R-4 | Visual drift (toggle width, animation) at pi-switch migration | LOW | Browser-use A/B compare screenshots; ±10% tolerance |
| R-5 | Data-test propagation broken in pi-* primitives — E2E selectors fail | MEDIUM | Per-primitive: confirm `data-test` attribute passes through host → native element |
| R-6 | Mass migration overwhelms review (1500 LOC one commit) | HIGH | Per-batch atomic commits of 5-8 pages; per-spec review |
| R-7 | Hidden `<select>`/`<textarea>` in dialog-side components (not just listed above) | MEDIUM | Re-grep `dialog.tokens.ts`-imported components post-Phase A |

